FBIS4-65714 "drweu099_b_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 BENELUX COUNTRIES The Netherlands Government Refuses Troops for Rwanda Government Refuses Troops for Rwanda LD2005181394 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1730 GMT 20 May 94 LD2005181394 Hilversum Radio Netherlands English BFN [Text] The Dutch Cabinet has announced that the security situation in Rwanda is so bad that, for the time being, the Netherlands is not to provide troops for a UN peacekeeping force. Apparently, the gruesome murder of 10 Belgian blue helmets in Rwanda last month was an important factor in the Dutch Cabinet's decision. Rwanda used to be a Belgian colony and the Dutch ministers fear that Dutch soldiers could be mistaken for Belgians.
